ion:
  id: 08-research/july-01-2026-yawn-bot-feedback-loop-lock
  title: july 01 2026 yawn bot feedback loop lock
  type: source-summary
  status: seed-canon
  updated: 2026-07-01

source_context:
  The user asked to run and verify the yawn.bot automation with a meaningful
  suggestion, describing a feedback loop where enough feedback creates a solid
  thesis, risks are weighed, and then yawn.bot can commit.

primary_claims:
  - feedback should not become a commit until it forms a coherent thesis
  - the thesis should be weighed against risks and dissent
  - yawn.bot should be able to recommend and eventually commit bounded changes
  - authority must remain explicit so the bot does not mutate the repo from weak signals

implementation_decision:
  Added automation/yawn.bot.feedback-loop.yawn and
  records/yawn.bot-verification-2026-07-01.yawn. The first verification found
  no live external feedback, issues, or pull requests, so the meaningful
  suggestion was to encode the feedback-to-commit gate itself.

proof:
  source:
    - user-message
    - manual-yawn-bot-verification-run
  claim: This file captures the yawn.bot feedback-loop and commit-gate requirement.
  proof_state: source-summary
